East coast is shit, the cities are old, dirty, run down, and crime ridden; do not recommend. Lack any modern features you see in European, Asia countries or California.
I used to like snow as a kid and they are still beautiful to see but it gets really annoying when you have to head out...
As a kid, I wake up see the snow and I'm so happy. No school being the best part and then it all cozy with the entire family together. Good times.
Then you get older, you go to school/work deep in snow, slipping on ice, freezing your face off, being late, dirty grey slush everywhere. Not fun AT ALL. The dark grey skies is really depressing too, i much prefer a much warmer place.

I feel for ya though, but I'm one that couldn't survive the hot weather that far south. Although most can't handle how cold it gets up here either ^^; I love it but I'm a weirdo

snippet.textDisplay: It's not just because you were a kid.  I'm 45, and I can assure you, winter is genuinely the best time of year, all round.  In fact, the only time I ever liked summer was when I was a kid, and that was just because there was no school for two and a half months.  As an adult, I have really no use for summer, and every time it comes around I find myself thinking about moving north to some place that doesn't really HAVE summer.  Nunavut, perhaps.  But there's a problem:  it's hard to find a job up there.

snippet.textDisplay:
Here in western Washington, it's either rain or cold. Very rarely do we get both to make snow. We might get a couple days to a week of snow each year.

However, parts of eastern Washington and definitely the mountains will see snow more regularly.

Leavenworth is especially beautiful for the holidays, though I haven't been in a while. A Bavarian style town, with German, Bavarian and Christmas music playing out in the streets, surrounded by mountains, and everything is blanketed with fresh snow. 🏔️☺️
